    <h1 id="summary">Summary</h1>
    <p>AncesTrim <span class="citation">(Niskanen, Salmela, and Lohi 2017)</span> is a Python tool for trimming complex pedigrees. Some pedigree data can have an inherently complicated structure with a high level of inbreeding, which makes visualization of such data difficult. AncesTrim reduces the complexity of pedigrees while preserving critical relatedness structures, allowing the pedigree to be displayed in a more efficient way.</p>
